• Neutrons: 45% when operating from 200C - 500C

The prompt gamma and neutron dosimetry in the UDR-14 was designed to detect prompt gammas and neutrons from a nuclear blast. The firmware does not allow it to record any measurements from only prompt gammas, like those from a flash X-ray machine. Prompt gammas will only be measured when they are accompanied by an intense neutron radiation field, minimum 150 cGy/hr. Neutron dose measurements will also be ignored if the neutron dose rate is less than 150 cGy/hr.
• Sleep Mode - about 1,500 hours
